    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>A sheath typically of very thin rubber, worn over the penis during sexual intercourse to prevent contraception or sexually transmitted disease.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000046684/Random House Unabridged Dictionary (1993)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Omhulsels, gewoonlijk van zeer dun rubber, die bij geslachtsgemeenschap om de penis worden gedragen teneinde bevruchting of seksueel overdraagbare ziekten te voorkomen.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099102/Van Dale Ne-En (1991)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Eine Hülle, typischerweise aus sehr dünnem Kautschuk, die während des Geschlechtsverkehrs über dem Penis getragen wird, um einer Empfängnis oder sexuell übertragbaren Krankheiten vorzubeugen.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>German</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
